The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | German unit in Howrah 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      German unit in Howrah 
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, Dec. 12: W. Hunger Hydraulics India today inaugurated its first manufacturing unit in the country at the Poly Park in Howrah.        
	The German company, specialising in polymer-based seals and bearings for hydraulic cylinders, will start production in February 2010.        
	The Hunger group has invested around Rs 13 crore to set up this unit in Bengal, chairperson Ingrid Hunger said. The factory, built on 0.6 acres within the industrial park, was inaugurated by chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee.         
	Once it starts production, it will help other industries come up in this part of the country, said Bhattacharjee.        
	The Hunger Group started its operation in Calcutta in 1987 as a wholly owned non-resident office. W. Hunger Hydraulics India  a wholly owned subsidiary  was formed in 2006. In 2007, the foundation stone was laid.        
	I am happy to know that two years since I laid the foundation stone, the factory with 30 workers is ready to operate, said Bhattacharjee.        
	Hunger said the company was looking to tap the large skilled labour in Bengal.                                                                                                                                       
